<subSubSection id="CAB910D400543C6ADE0D361286F39FD2" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="3EA8BF009041AC7192C273A08D1D976C" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E013127979F625B0BE7ADF4A91BC74A2" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
A new record for the Greek flora. 
<taxonomicName id="D86BCA583266874EB0241860A691E0BC" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Anthericum" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Anthericum ramosum" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ramosum">
<emphasis id="0A20E0DF565FB2A6B87E2479F57C0A67" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Anthericum ramosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the generitype of 
<taxonomicName id="EEC8CBE73E6D47879667FA59F21ED224" class="Liliopsida" family="Asparagaceae" genus="Anthericum" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Anthericum" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="669B4F64858A8D92EE750DB998248EBC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Anthericum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., has a predominantly central European distribution that reaches parts of Russia and Asiatic Turkey to the East (
<bibRefCitation id="CEA6AD7E28840558F1B997D78D5EA51B" author="Webb, D. A." journalOrPublisher="Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7670161" refString="Webb, D. A., 1980. Flora Europaea Vol. 5. Cambridge University Press, Cambridge" title="Flora Europaea Vol. 5" year="1980">Webb 1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="0A933215B8C56D915E43B4DBA8C1BDF9" author="Matthews, V. A." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668927" refString="Matthews, V. A., 1984. Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands Vol 8. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Flora of Turkey and the East Aegean Islands Vol 8" year="1984">Matthews 1984</bibRefCitation>
). Although reported &quot; 
<emphasis id="44CDCC15FF761DB3A7C8FDE34B8D230B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">in Europae australioris</emphasis>
&quot; by 
<bibRefCitation id="82042C744906D1BE1D9AE807ABE5C7E3" author="Linnaeus, C." journalOrPublisher="Laurentius Salvius ,, Holmiae" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668889" refString="Linnaeus, C., 1762. Species Plantarum Tomus 1. Editio secunda. Laurentius Salvius,, Holmiae" title="Species Plantarum Tomus 1. Editio secunda" year="1762">Linnaeus (1762)</bibRefCitation>
(type: Herb. Linn. no. 432.6, LINN!, see 
<bibRefCitation id="B55B45E5EFF5D0AEE931961A3D0E198F" author="Jarvis, C. E." journalOrPublisher="Regnum Veg." pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="1 - 100" refId="B7733090" refString="Jarvis, C. E., Barrie, F. R., Allan, D. M., Reveal, J. L., 1993. A list of Linnaean generic names and their types. Regnum Veg. 127: 1 - 100" title="A list of Linnaean generic names and their types" volume="127" year="1993">Jarvis et al. 1993</bibRefCitation>
) it has not been reported in Greece so far. Our specimen from the foothills of Mt. Orvilos (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0A51FF747019854BD0FB16DD6CCDBAC3" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F7671038" captionText="Figure 1. Anthericum ramosum from Mt Orvilos (photo: K. Goula)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/639590" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">1</figureCitation>
), at a linear distance of ca. 5.5 km south of the Greek-Bulgarian border, has a paniculate inflorescence with 2-6, 6.5-11 cm long branches, white tepals 9-12 mm long, a straight style and an almost spherical, obtuse capsule 5-5.5 x 4.5-6 mm with a short remnant of the style base. It differs considerably from 
<taxonomicName id="F03D337BB87083309FD8E01829B62855" genus="A." lsidName="A. liliago" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" rank="species" species="liliago">
<emphasis id="41B5801ECCE22F78D7F78958FDE4C1FA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">A. liliago</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L., which is widespread in Greece, being reported from the south mainland (north Peloponnisos) to the northern borders (
<bibRefCitation id="37823813B44DD8B989123C55734027D8" author="Andersson, I. A." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667715" refString="Andersson, I. A., 1991. Mountain Flora of Greece 2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Mountain Flora of Greece 2" year="1991">Andersson 1991a</bibRefCitation>
). The latter has a simple or sparingly branched inflorescence, larger tepals (13-20 mm), a somewhat curved style and a longer (8-11 x 6-7 mm) capsule with an acute apex.
</paragraph>
